name: Nokia 5.4
description: Nokia 5.4 is officially announced on December 15, 2020. The display size is 6.39 inches with an IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen that provides a resolution of 720 x 1520 pixels.

name: POCO C3
description: The phone comes with a 6.53-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 720x1600 pixels and an aspect ratio of 20:9. Poco C3 is powered by an octa-core MediaTek Helio G35 processor. It comes with 3GB of RAM.

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY A3 CORE
description: The Samsung Galaxy A3 Core sports a 5.3-inch HD+ (720x1,480 pixels) TFT LCD display with 16:9 aspect ratio. The entry-level handset runs on Android Go edition. Under the hood, the Samsung Galaxy A3 Core comes equipped with an unnamed quad-core SoC that is clocked at 1.5GHz.

name: APPLE IPAD PRO 11
description: Apple iPad Pro (11-inch) 2020 Wi-Fi tablet was launched on 18th March 2020. The tablet comes with a 11.00-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 1668x2388 pixels at a pixel density of 264 pixels per inch (ppi).

name: BLACKVIEW A80S
description: Blackview A80s has a 6.22 inchedisplay, with a processor speed of 1.3 Quad-core GHz Cortex-A53). The Operating System is Android 10. It has a RAM size of 4 GB, a ROM of 64 GB.

name: POCO X3
description: The POCO X3 and POCO X3 NFC are Android-based smartphones developed by Xiaomi, announced on 7 and 22 September 2020. The phone has a FHD+ IPS LCD 6.67 display, a 64 MP wide, 13 MP ultra-wide, 2 MP macro, and 2 MP depth camera, a 5160 mAh battery, 8gb ram and a side-mounted fingerprint sensor.

name: SAMSUNG GALAXY A12
description: Samsung Galaxy A12 is powered by a 1.8GHz octa-core MediaTek Helio P35 (MT6765) processor that features 4 cores clocked at 1.8GHz and 4 cores clocked at 23GHz. It comes with 4GB of RAM.

name: LENOVO TAB M8
description: The tablet comes with a 8.00-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 720x1280 pixels. Lenovo Tab M8 is powered by a 2GHz octa-core MediaTek Helio A22 processor.
